{"type":"FeatureCollection","features":[{"type":"Feature","geometry":{"type":"GeometryCollection","geometries":[{"type":"Point","coordinates":[143.48598770242108,-38.50170838102764]},{"type":"Polygon","coordinates":[[[143.4059935007608,-38.46222731041315],[143.43963913064852,-38.44071786212866],[143.50075058083993,-38.4455580470197],[143.56392196755635,-38.477817650699244],[143.57010177713144,-38.51973356232801],[143.54881576638488,-38.55088599074463],[143.50349716287033,-38.55840352119509],[143.44032577615386,-38.56269889992663],[143.40187362771073,-38.53907114041147],[143.4046202097501,-38.50630163126035],[143.4059935007608,-38.46222731041315]]]}]},"properties":{"feedType":"warning","cap":{"category":"Fire","event":"Bushfire","eventCode":"bushFire","urgency":"Unknown","severity":"Unknown","certainty":"Observed","contact":"birgitte.hutchens@delwp.vic.gov.au","senderName":"Forest Fire Management Victoria","responseType":"None"},"sourceOrg":"EMV","sourceId":"41700","sourceFeed":"cop-cap","sourceTitle":"Community Information","id":"41700","category1":"Community Update","category2":"Fire","status":"Unknown","name":"Community Information","action":"Stay Informed","statewide":"N","location":"between the townships of  Irrewillipe, Kawarren, Lovat, Wimba, Charleys Creek, Carlisle River and covers the township of Gellibrand","created":"2026-03-08T14:38:34+11:00","updated":"2026-03-08T14:38:57+11:00","webHeadline":null,"webBody":"<div style=\"margin-bottom:20px\">This <b>Community Information</b>&nbsp;message is being issued for <span title=\"warning_locality\" class=\"param\" contenteditable=\"false\">between the townships of  Irrewillipe, Kawarren, Lovat, Wimba, Charleys Creek, Carlisle River and covers the township of Gellibrand</span>.&nbsp;<div><div><ul><li>There is a bushfire at&nbsp;<span title=\"warning_incident_location\" class=\"param\" contenteditable=\"false\">Carlisle River</span>&nbsp;that is&nbsp;<span class=\"editable editable-click editable-unsaved\" data-type=\"select\" data-emptytext=\"[status]\" data-value=\"1\" contenteditable=\"false\" style=\"display: inline;\" data-source=\"{&quot;0&quot;:&quot;not yet under control&quot;,&quot;1&quot;:&quot;under control&quot;}\" data-original-title=\"\" title=\"\">under control</span>.</li><li>This Community Information replaces the message issued on 4 March 2026.</li><li>Firefighters\nare currently patrolling this fire.</li><li>Please observe all track closures.&nbsp;</li></ul></div></div></div><div style=\"font-size: 120%; font-weight: bold; margin-bottom:20px\">There is currently no threat to the community however be aware of crews and heavy machinery working to rehabilitate affected tracks and stabilising areas of the fire ground.</div><div style=\"margin-bottom:20px\">This message was issued\nby <span title=\"warning_issuing_agency\" class=\"param\" contenteditable=\"false\">Forest Fire Management Victoria</span>.<div><br></div><div><br></div><div><b>Use multiple sources to stay informed:&nbsp;</b></div><div><ul><li><a href=\"http://emergency.vic.gov.au/respond/\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\">www.emergency.vic.gov.au</a></li><li><a href=\"https://vicemergency.zendesk.com/hc/en-gb/articles/115001055007-What-is-the-VicEmergency-Hotline-\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\">\n VicEmergency Hotline</a>&nbsp;- freecall 1800 226 226</li><li><a href=\"https://vicemergency.zendesk.com/hc/en-gb/articles/230492607-What-is-the-VicEmergency-app-\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: white;\">VicEmergency app</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/vicemergency\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\">\nFacebook</a> or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/vicemergency\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: white;\">Twitter</a>&nbsp;(#vicfires).</li><li>Tune in to ABC Local Radio, commercial and designated community radio stations, or Sky News TV. </li></ul><div><b>Accessibility: </b></div></div><div>The following services can\nhelp you, or someone you know, access information during an emergency. </div><div><ul><li>\n To access this information\n     in other languages call the <a href=\"https://www.tisnational.gov.au/\" title=\"Translating and Interpreting Service\" target=\"_blank\">Translating and Interpreting Service</a>&nbsp;on&nbsp;131 450&nbsp;(freecall) and ask\n     them to call VicEmergency Hotline. &nbsp;\n </li><li>If you are deaf, hard of\nhearing, or have a speech/communication impairment contact <a href=\"https://www.accesshub.gov.au/about-the-nrs/nrs-call-numbers-and-links\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\">National Relay Service&nbsp;</a>for assistance\nand ask them to call the VicEmergency Hotline.&nbsp; </li></ul></div></div>","text":"COMMUNITY INFORMATION - BUSHFIRE - Stay Informed\nIncident Location: Carlisle River\nIssue Date: Sunday 08 March 2026, 02:38 pm\nNext Update: Friday 13 March 2026, 02:40 pm\n\nMore details at http://emergency.vic.gov.au/respond/#!/warning/41700/moreinfo\n\nThis Community Information message is being issued for between the townships of  Irrewillipe, Kawarren, Lovat, Wimba, Charleys Creek, Carlisle River and covers the township of Gellibrand. \n- There is a bushfire at Carlisle River that is under control.\n- This Community Information replaces the message issued on 4 March 2026.\n- Firefighters are currently patrolling this fire.\n- Please observe all track closures. \n\n\nThere is currently no threat to the community however be aware of crews and heavy machinery working to rehabilitate affected tracks and stabilising areas of the fire ground.\n\n","sizeFmt":null,"incidentFeatures":[{"properties":{"feedType":"incident","sourceOrg":"EMV","sourceId":"41700","sourceFeed":"cop-cap","sourceTitle":"Community Information","id":"41700","category1":"Fire","category2":"Bushfire","name":"Community Information","location":"Carlisle River","created":"2026-03-08T14:38:34+11:00","updated":"2026-03-08T14:38:57+11:00","webHeadline":null,"sizeFmt":null}}]}},{"properties":{"status":"Patrolled",